data.title: Meaghan Doyle - 2006 - Women's Soccer
data.meta_description: Meaghan Doyle (22) D  - AS A SENIOR:  Started all 19 games for the Mount defense as a senior...Recorded two shots on the seasons...Usually matched up with opposing
data.text:
AS A SENIOR: Started all 19 games for the Mount defense as a senior...Recorded two shots on the seasons...Usually matched up with opposing team's top scorer.

AS A JUNIOR: Started 17 of 18 games on the season...Tallied first collegiate goal in the Mount's 10-0 win over Delaware State...Notched an assist in the Mount's 3-2 loss to East Tennessee State...Emerged as one of the Mount's top defenders.

AS A SOPHOMORE:Made nine appearances last season, including two starts... Notched her first collegiate start in a 2-1 loas against Lafayette on Sept. 4, 2004... Recorded her first career assist in a 2-0 victory against St. Peter's on Sept. 17, 2004... Tallied a shot in a 3-2 loss at Wagner on Sept. 24, 2004.

AS A FRESHMAN:Appeared in three contests in her freshman campaign... Made collegiate debut against Grambling State on Sept. 5, 2003... Played against Delaware State on Sept. 17, 2003 and against Monmouth on Oct. 29, 2003.

HIGH SCHOOL: A three-year letterwinner for the Seton Keough soccer team... Served as team capain in her senior year... Earned MVP honors as a junior and a senior... Named to the Interscholastic Athletic Association of Maryland (IAAM) All-Star second team...Received All-Baltimore County/City second-team honors by the Baltimore Sun... A member on the women's lacrosse team, helping lead her team to a 2002 IAAM B-Conference Championship... Volunteered for the special education summer program and at the Howard County General Hospital.
